IXWebsocket has CI for Windows + TLS disabled.
When totally cleaning the build dir those 2 lines are going to be needed in "IXSocketMbedTLS.cpp" file - otherwise compiler will throw 8 errors.
#include <mbedtls/version.h>
#include <psa/crypto.h>

1. Generate project:
cmake -G "Ninja" -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=clang++ -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DUSE_TLS=1 -DUSE_WS=1 -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE="C:/vcpkg/vcpkg/scripts/buildsystems/vcpkg.cmake" -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=1 ..
"-DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE" - configure it for yourself. I am using vcpkg and this works for me.
"-DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=1" - when set it generates compile_commands.json file. Create a symbolic link to this file so that clangd can use it:
mklink "compile_commands.json" "build/compile_commands.json"

2. Build project
cmake --build .
